OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,382,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38102
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F381A1781531287
OL,3,CEsso fined #1 million after 'partial
OL,4,Ccollapse' caused 33 hour long gas leak
OL,6,FEmergency measures were used by Esso
OL,7,Fto manage the collapse, including
OL,8,Fwater curtains, to reduce the spread
OL,9,Fof the flammable gas.
OL,11,FFollowing an investigation by HSE, it
OL,12,Fwas found that the collapse occurred
OL,13,Fdue to the corrosion of the tower,
OL,14,Fwhich had taken place over many years.
OL,16,FIt had first been identified in 2010,
OL,17,Fbut ESSO had 'failed to take
OL,18,Fappropriate action to control the
OL,19,Frisk', HSE found out.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G2/5
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,382,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38103
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F381A1781531287
OL,3,CEsso fined #1 million after 'partial
OL,4,Ccollapse' caused 33 hour long gas leak
OL,6,FCompanies must ensure the integrity of
OL,7,Fplant and pipework is maintained and
OL,8,Fthat equipment is kept in a safe
OL,9,Fcondition, which includes identifying
OL,10,Fand managing risks such as corrosion
OL,11,Fto prevent loss of containment of
OL,12,Fhazardous substances.
OL,14,FEsso pleased guilty to breaching
OL,15,FSection 3(1) of the Health and Safety
OL,16,Fat Work etc. Act 1974. The company was
OL,17,Ffined #1 million and ordered to pay
OL,18,F#12,277 in costs at Southampton
OL,19,FMagistrates' Court on 12 June 2026.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G3/5
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,382,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38104
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F381A1781531287
OL,3,CEsso fined #1 million after 'partial
OL,4,Ccollapse' caused 33 hour long gas leak
OL,6,FAmanda Huff, an Inspector in HSE's
OL,7,Fspecialist Chemicals, Explosives &
OL,8,FMajor Hazards Division, said: "This
OL,9,Fincident resulted in the uncontrolled
OL,10,Frelease of a large quantity of
OL,11,Fflammable gas, which exposed workers
OL,12,Fto very real and potentially life-
OL,13,Fthreatening risks.
OL,15,F"The underlying cause was a failure to
OL,16,Fproperly manage the integrity of plant
OL,17,Fand equipment, despite corrosion being
OL,18,Fidentified many years earlier.
OL,26,@pD@_OUwD@AOU
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G4/5
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,382,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38105
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F381A1781531287
OL,3,CEsso fined #1 million after 'partial
OL,4,Ccollapse' caused 33 hour long gas leak
OL,6,F"Workers and the wider public have
OL,7,Fevery right to assume that sites
OL,8,Fprocessing large quantities of highly
OL,9,Fflammable chemicals are being properly
OL,10,Fmanaged ` and it is vital for
OL,11,Fcompanies to make sure robust systems
OL,12,Fare in place to maintain critical
OL,13,Finfrastructure safely.
OL,15,F"This incident could have been far
OL,16,Fworse, and today's sentence reflects
OL,17,Fthe seriousness of the breaches our
OL,18,Finvestigation uncovered."
OL,26,@nD@AOUwD@AOUzD@YO]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G5/5
